textBeforeTable: Noack's Career Statistics   PERSONAL: Full name is Patrick David Noack... parents are Jim and Nancy Noack... has one older sister Jenny... major is history. HIGH SCHOOL: Attended Benicia High School where he played under Aja Roaper and Ross Spiritosanto... helped team finish second in the league with a 22-4 record as a senior... scored 127 goals his senior season... led the team in goals, steals, and assists his senior and junior years... also swam and played basketball. AS A FRESHMAN IN 2003-04: Saw action in all 16 contests... has two goals and five assists on the season... scored first collegiate goal against Cal Maritime... added second goal against UC San Diego at the UC Davis Shootout... also posted seven steals. AS A SOPHOMORE IN 2004-05: Appeared in 27 contests... scored seven goals on the season and had six assists... scored first goal of the season against Pepperdine at the Inland Empire Classic... netted goals in two consecutive contests against Chapman and 15th-ranked Pacific... had a season-high two steals against LaVerne... scored against Navy in the Nor Cal Tournament...netted another goal and had a steal against No. 13 UC Davis...drew a kick out and had a season-best two goals against UC Santa Cruz.
